---
title: Creamy Parmesan Beef Cavatappi with Zucchini & Lemon
description: Creamy, zesty lemon-Parmesan sauce makes for a luxurious pasta night! You’ll whip up this sumptuous sauce and stir in ground beef sautéed with garlic and a blend of Italian herbs. Toss in tender zucchini and al dente curly cavatappi pasta, then load up your bowls and sprinkle with extra Parmesan for a meal that hits all the right notes.

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67043a3199e8e2a18bd761ec-51abbefe.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67043a3199e8e2a18bd761ec-en-US.pdf
cuisine: Southern Europe
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 25 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 850 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 76 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 770 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-parmesan-beef-cavatappi-67043a3199e8e2a18bd761ec
course: main course
---

Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); cut into 1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 2 cups pasta cooking water (4 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; season with @Italian seasoning{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use more Italian seasoning in the next step.) Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes} (7-10 minutes for 4).

Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}; season with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @Italian seasoning{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper.

> Be sure to measure the Italian Seasoning—we sent more!

Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @cheese roux concentrate{1%ounce} to pan with beef. Stir to combine.

Stir in 1 1⁄2 cups reserved pasta cooking water (2 cups for 4 servings) and bring to a boil. Once boiling, reduce heat to medium and simmer, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

> TIP: If pasta isn't done cooking yet, ladle pasta water directly from pot.

Reduce heat to medium low; whisk in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} until melted and combined. Season lightly with pepper.

Add drained cavatappi, zucchini, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of lemon zest to pan with sauce.

Turn off heat; continue stirring until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce, ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time.

Taste and season with salt, pepper, and more lemon juice if desired.

Divide pasta between shallow #bowls{} and top with remaining Parmesan. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.